		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Aug 24th 4:38 PM2004 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=1093367361687828954&num=5&post=1&replyto=10933798974193262"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=10933798974193262></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=247125"><span id="Scholar">Jiggidyjay the Quick</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />1950 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.11]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>It depends on what exactly he means by nerfed. A lot of things can change that some people will consider positive nerfs and others negative nerfs. Recently, they lowered the amount of aggro that our chants caused significantly. That could be considered a positive nerf for swarm kiters, as it means less running the swarm through your pet when they aggro on you instead of him. For raiding bards, this could bad, as that is sometimes the tactic used to kite adds away from a particular mob the raid is going after. As far as AE kiting, they changed the extended notes AA to only work with beneficial songs. That was really too overpowering. I can't think of anything in the lower levels that has been changed, other then pathing/stacking issues maybe. There were some bad stacking issues (and sticking issues, as in to trees) with the change to Direct X 9, causing a lot of grief for AEers, but I believe most of those have been fixed. I don't AE much anymore personally. I'd much rather group in BoT then kite in Nadox. Ask you friend exactly what nerf he's referring too and post back here... I'm interested in what he was talking about too.</p>
