		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sat, Aug 28th 6:37 PM2004 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=1093367361687828954&num=5&post=1&replyto=1093732637142929682"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1093732637142929682></a></small>| <span id="fs8">Edited: 2004-08-28 18:40:26</span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=61546"><span id="Sage">Slipskin</span></a><b><span id="Sage"><br>Sage</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />1262 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.70]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Slipskin&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>What he may be refering to is the charm kite nerf.&nbsp;&nbsp;SoE lowered the amount of experience awarded to a player if a charmed mob was used as a pet to kill another mob.  I think the experience loss is about 25%.   <br /> <br />SoE, in general, is very annoyed at the concept of kiting.  The idea of killing any mob with little or no risk to yourself just makes their teeth grind.  This is why, in EQ2, SoE has instroduced combat modes.  These prevent kiting by slowing the movement speed of anyone engaged in combat of any kind with a mob.  If you release the combat mode to run away you lose any experience you would have been rewarded for killing it.   <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sat Aug 28 18:40:12 2004 by Slipskin</span></i></p>
