		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.12]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Luckily for us, that nerf didn't hurt bards too much. It hurt chanters A LOT and druids to an extent, but bards kinda get away with murder here, at least when swarm kiting. This is why... <br /> <br />The nerf only applies to charmed pets killing another mob. If the pet does more then 50 percent of the damage to the mob, you only get 50 pct of the experience. If you don't do at least 1 point of damage to the mob, you will not get any experience. The good thing for us, when swarm kiting, is that it's not our pet killing another mob, it's other mobs (almost) killing our pet. When then break charm and chant the mob down the last 1-20 pct. We do get full experience for the kill. This will not apply though if you are doing normal charm kiting, where you charm one mob and sic it on another and help it out with dots. The nerfed experience rules will apply in that case, so if that's what you're wanting to do, you better make sure you're doing more damage then your pet.</p>
