		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.12]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I don't think he was referring to the upcoming AE nerf. They kind of snuck that one in on us. The snuck it onto the test server and didn't mention anything about it, then this week tell us it's going live on the 14th, regardless of how we feel (it is a nerf afterall), but they &quot;may&quot; (as in never) change it back or to something else if we can give them ideas on what can be done. Of course, they don't like any of our ideas and think they're all too much work... the big problem here is the precedent they are setting. Part of the nerf is that detrimental AE songs will have a reduced radius if you are moving. We don't only use detrimental songs for AE kiting though. We do have AE slow/snare and it IS used in SOME raid/group situations. This will pretty much eliminate that, as it's very rare that a mob will stand perfectly still for you while you beat on it. So, by requiring that we stand perfectly still, they are setting the precedent for this action to be taken on any other bard songs that they feel are overpowering in the future. You can be sure that this will probably be implemented in some form on PvP servers as well. It's a sad day for bards, wether you AE kite or not.</p>
